00:23:04,230 --> 00:23:05,070
Go ahead.

294
00:23:15,780 --> 00:23:17,620
If you have any questions, ask me directly.

295
00:23:18,230 --> 00:23:19,270
Why fish for that from the child?

296
00:23:22,950 --> 00:23:24,510
I'm concerned about both of you.

297
00:23:26,430 --> 00:23:27,670
How is that fishing?

298
00:23:28,820 --> 00:23:30,540
Besides, you've taught her how to answer

299
00:23:31,820 --> 00:23:33,990
about the things you don't want me to know,

300
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,140
right?

301
00:23:37,270 --> 00:23:39,060
Do you think I would teach the child to lie?

302
00:23:40,990 --> 00:23:41,950
Fang Xiewen,

303
00:23:41,950 --> 00:23:43,190
what are you thinking about all day?

304
00:23:54,380 --> 00:23:55,230
Did you get your nails done?

305
00:24:06,430 --> 00:24:07,270
Why?

306
00:24:10,300 --> 00:24:11,140
I like it.

307
00:24:15,540 --> 00:24:17,230
Daddy, I washed my hands.

308
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:18,750
I want to eat the cake.

309
00:24:27,230 --> 00:24:28,070
Alright.

310
00:24:28,140 --> 00:24:29,100
Taichu, sit down.

311
00:24:29,750 --> 00:24:32,270
I will give you some cake. Here.

312
00:24:38,860 --> 00:24:39,950
Is it your favorite?

313
00:24:45,670 --> 00:24:46,990
Then sit still.

314
00:24:47,030 --> 00:24:47,870
Taichu.

315
00:24:53,100 --> 00:24:56,030
(Inbox)

316
00:24:56,030 --> 00:24:57,100
Do you still want to ride a big horse?

317
00:24:58,300 --> 00:24:59,820
Then sit tight.

318
00:25:06,540 --> 00:25:07,540
Why is it ringing?

319
00:25:08,580 --> 00:25:10,030
Someone's calling you.

320
00:25:10,990 --> 00:25:12,430
Daddy, you're getting a shot.

321
00:25:12,430 --> 00:25:13,270
A shot?

322
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,100
- Give me a shot.
- Taichu.

323
00:25:16,670 --> 00:25:17,710
Time to sleep.

324
00:25:18,510 --> 00:25:19,350
Come.

325
00:25:20,340 --> 00:25:21,180
Taichu, tonight,

326
00:25:21,340 --> 00:25:24,030
do you want to sleep with Mommy and Daddy?

327
00:25:25,620 --> 00:25:26,460
Yes.

328
00:25:27,750 --> 00:25:28,820
She can sleep by herself.

329
00:25:30,510 --> 00:25:31,350
Taichu,

330
00:25:31,510 --> 00:25:33,140
do you want Daddy to tell you a story?

331
00:25:33,430 --> 00:25:34,270
Yes.

332
00:25:34,510 --> 00:25:37,340
I want to hear the story
of Little Red Riding Hood.

333
00:25:37,430 --> 00:25:40,060
Then ask Mommy to come and sleep with us.

334
00:25:40,950 --> 00:25:41,790
Okay.

335
00:25:42,950 --> 00:25:43,990
Mommy,

336
00:25:44,510 --> 00:25:46,710
let's sleep with Dad.

337
00:25:46,780 --> 00:25:47,620
Okay?

338
00:25:55,710 --> 00:25:56,550
Get into the blanket.

339
00:25:56,710 --> 00:25:57,780
Under the blanket.

340
00:26:06,950 --> 00:26:07,910
Little Red Riding Hood.

341
00:26:09,140 --> 00:26:11,620
Let me tell you the story
of Little Red Riding Hood.

342
00:26:15,470 --> 00:26:16,470
Once upon a time,

343
00:26:16,750 --> 00:26:19,750
there was a lovely little girl.

344
00:26:20,380 --> 00:26:22,580
She liked to wear a red velvet cap

345
00:26:22,860 --> 00:26:25,510
her grandmother gave her.

346
00:26:26,430 --> 00:26:29,620
So everyone called her Little Red Riding Hood.

347
00:26:30,100 --> 00:26:30,990
One day,

348
00:26:31,470 --> 00:26:32,670
her mother asked her to bring food

349
00:26:32,860 --> 00:26:35,100
to her grandmother who lived in the forest

350
00:26:36,030 --> 00:26:38,430
and reminded her

351
00:26:39,190 --> 00:26:40,030
not to stray from the path.

352
00:26:44,270 --> 00:26:47,300
In the forest, Little Red Riding Hood
met the big bad wolf.

353
00:27:09,470 --> 00:27:10,310
Are you still angry?

354
00:27:12,990 --> 00:27:15,620
You can't avoid me every night.

355
00:27:34,140 --> 00:27:35,100
I don't want a second child.

356
00:28:23,540 --> 00:28:25,740
(Home)

357
00:28:31,710 --> 00:28:32,550
Come in.

358
00:28:43,670 --> 00:28:44,510
Don't worry.

359
00:28:44,820 --> 00:28:45,860
I'm not here to argue.

360
00:28:47,580 --> 00:28:48,420
Sit down.

361
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:51,750
There's nothing left to argue about.

362
00:28:53,230 --> 00:28:54,950
The merger with Tianlangxing

363
00:28:55,950 --> 00:28:56,790
is decided.

364
00:29:04,230 --> 00:29:05,070
Fang,

365
00:29:06,430 --> 00:29:07,270
I've decided to leave.

366
00:29:12,030 --> 00:29:12,870
You were right.

367
00:29:13,750 --> 00:29:15,510
You control this company,

368
00:29:15,990 --> 00:29:17,140
so I must go.

369
00:29:24,380 --> 00:29:25,230
After the contract is signed,

370
00:29:25,910 --> 00:29:26,990
I'll buy

371
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:30,030
all your shares back

372
00:29:30,580 --> 00:29:31,470
at Tianlangxing's valuation.

373
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:33,380
If you're not assured,

374
00:29:33,580 --> 00:29:34,860
we can draft an agreement first.

375
00:29:36,190 --> 00:29:37,710
No need. I trust you.

376
00:29:43,950 --> 00:29:44,790
Fang,

377
00:29:45,710 --> 00:29:47,190
you can buy my shares,

378
00:29:48,540 --> 00:29:49,380
but

379
00:29:50,300 --> 00:29:52,140
don't buy out our friendship.

380
00:29:52,430 --> 00:29:53,620
Is that okay?

381
00:30:00,140 --> 00:30:00,980
I can't afford it.

382
00:30:04,990 --> 00:30:06,030
We'll have chances to work together

383
00:30:08,670 --> 00:30:09,750
in the future, right?

384
00:30:17,030 --> 00:30:17,870
I'm leaving.

385
00:30:20,860 --> 00:30:21,700
Lin Hao.

386
00:30:28,030 --> 00:30:29,190
I just want to know.

387
00:30:31,380 --> 00:30:32,670
Isn't it good to have money?

388
00:30:36,470 --> 00:30:37,860
I don't understand

389
00:30:38,950 --> 00:30:40,910
why you always want to take risks.

390
00:30:41,620 --> 00:30:42,950
Can't you just enjoy

391
00:30:43,270 --> 00:30:44,780
the pleasure of being rich?

392
00:30:48,100 --> 00:30:49,100
Maybe it is

393
00:30:49,100 --> 00:30:50,670
about finding my own limits.

394
00:30:51,580 --> 00:30:52,420
Yes.

395
00:30:52,780 --> 00:30:54,990
Being rich is impressive to others,

396
00:30:55,950 --> 00:30:57,270
but I feel

397
00:30:57,270 --> 00:30:59,340
I can do things greater than making money.

398
00:31:02,510 --> 00:31:03,540
See you, Fang.

399
00:31:30,750 --> 00:31:31,590
Come in.

400
00:31:37,030 --> 00:31:37,870
Tina.

401
00:31:41,910 --> 00:31:42,990
Why are you here?

402
00:31:43,820 --> 00:31:46,060
You got married in the morning
and came to work in the afternoon.

403
00:31:46,060 --> 00:31:47,620
Squeezing in a wedding like this.

404
00:31:48,510 --> 00:31:49,350
Here.

405
00:31:49,470 --> 00:31:51,060
- Congratulations on your wedding.
- Thank you.

406
00:31:52,100 --> 00:31:52,940
Sit down.

407
00:31:53,670 --> 00:31:54,540
How are you?

408
00:31:55,780 --> 00:31:58,540
This place looks the same as before.

409
00:31:58,540 --> 00:31:59,380
Not much has changed.

410
00:31:59,540 --> 00:32:00,380
I'm nostalgic.

411
00:32:03,990 --> 00:32:04,860
But I don't have alcohol here.

412
00:32:05,190 --> 00:32:06,820
I can see that. The liquor cabinet is gone.

413
00:32:08,060 --> 00:32:09,140
Huang Yimei went back to Shanghai?

414
00:32:09,620 --> 00:32:10,460
She left yesterday.

415
00:32:10,540 --> 00:32:11,510
In such a hurry?

416
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:12,870
That day,

417
00:32:13,230 --> 00:32:14,510
I told her about my plan

418
00:32:14,510 --> 00:32:15,780
to open an art gallery.

419
00:32:16,190 --> 00:32:17,470
I wanted to have a good talk with her.

420
00:32:18,030 --> 00:32:19,620
Both of us were trained by you.

421
00:32:19,620 --> 00:32:21,140
Why didn't you ask me about it?

422
00:32:21,670 --> 00:32:22,510
Ms. Su,

423
00:32:22,710 --> 00:32:24,470
